Gold Gains in London for First Day in Five; Silver Advances

-- B y   C h a n y a p o r n   C h a n j a r o e n
-- 
2011-03-30T07:17:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/gold-gains-in-london-for-first-day-in-five-silver-advances.html
Gold reversed an earlier decline,
rising for the first session in five. Silver also advanced.  Immediate-delivery bullion gained as much as 0.2 percent
at $1,421.38 an ounce and traded at $1,421.15 as of 8:11 a.m.
London time. The metal earlier fell as much as 0.3 percent.
Silver increased as much as 0.9 percent at $37.375.  To contact the reporter on this story:
